---
import FridayHarborLayout from '../../layouts/FridayHarborLayout.astro';
import { entries } from '../../data/friday-harbor';
const entry = entries.find(e => e.slug === '2026-04-27-1-23-million-eviction-filings')!;
---
<FridayHarborLayout entry={entry}>
  <figure slot="figure" class="evic-figure">
    <div class="evic-stage" id="stage" aria-label="Map of US eviction filings 2025">
      <p class="map-status">
        <span data-lang="en">Loading map...</span>
        <span data-lang="zh">地图加载中...</span>
      </p>
    </div>

    <figcaption data-lang="en">
      <b>1.23 million eviction cases across the 41 American cities the Eviction Lab tracks — roughly one filing for every 13 renter households.</b>
      The geography of those filings is not the geography of housing-market pressure. New York rents are world-class; New York's filing rate is 5%. Atlanta rents are roughly half of that; Atlanta's filing rate is 19.8%. The variable that explains the difference is <em>law</em>.
      <span class="legend-line">
        <span class="legend-swatch swatch-rtc"></span>
        <span><b>Sage tint</b> = state with stronger tenant protections (right-to-counsel, just-cause eviction, and/or aggressive sealing of records).</span>
      </span>
      <span class="legend-line">
        <span class="legend-swatch swatch-evic-major"></span>
        <span><b>Deep dots</b> mark the highest filing rates — Atlanta, Indianapolis, Richmond, Memphis, Charleston. Circle area is filing volume; colour is the rate.</span>
      </span>
    </figcaption>

    <figcaption data-lang="zh">
      <b>123 万起驱逐起诉，分布在 Eviction Lab 跟踪的 41 个美国城市——约每 13 户租客就有 1 起。</b>
      这片地理不是租房市场压力的地理。纽约租金在世界排名顶级，filing rate 是 5%；亚特兰大租金大约是纽约的一半，filing rate 是 19.8%。能解释这种差距的变量是<em>法律</em>。
      <span class="legend-line">
        <span class="legend-swatch swatch-rtc"></span>
        <span><b>淡绿底色</b>= 该州拥有较强的租客保护（法律咨询权、正当理由驱逐、或强力封存驱逐记录）。</span>
      </span>
      <span class="legend-line">
        <span class="legend-swatch swatch-evic-major"></span>
        <span><b>深色圆点</b>标出 filing rate 最高的城市——亚特兰大、印第安纳波利斯、里士满、孟菲斯、查尔斯顿。圆面积代表 filing 总量，颜色代表 filing rate。</span>
      </span>
    </figcaption>

    <aside class="evic-stats" aria-label="key 2025 eviction figures">
      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">1.23<small>&nbsp;M</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">eviction filings across 41 tracked US cities · 2025</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">123<small>&nbsp;万</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">起驱逐起诉 · 41 个被追踪美国城市合计 · 2025</span>
      </div>

      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">7.9<small>&nbsp;%</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">national average — one case per 13 renter households</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">7.9<small>&nbsp;%</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">全国平均——每 13 户租客 1 起</span>
      </div>

      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">19.8<small>&nbsp;%</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">peak (Atlanta) — one in five renters</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">19.8<small>&nbsp;%</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">最高 (亚特兰大) ——每 5 户租客 1 起</span>
      </div>

      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">~ 4<small>&nbsp;×</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">filing-rate gap between weakest- and strongest-protection states</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">约 4<small>&nbsp;×</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">最弱保护州与最强保护州之间的 filing rate 差</span>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </figure>

  <div slot="notebook-en">
    <p>
      Most evictions don't make headlines because they happen one at a time.
      The figure on this map is therefore unfamiliar even though it is enormous:
      1.23 million eviction cases were filed across 41 American cities last year,
      roughly one for every 13 renter households living in them. The map asks the
      reader to look at a number that is usually buried in a sentence.
    </p>
    <p>
      The dots are not where rent is highest. New York has some of the highest
      rents in the world and a 5% filing rate. Atlanta has roughly half of New
      York's median rent and a 19.8% rate — one in five Atlanta renters faced
      an eviction filing last year. Philadelphia, similar story: real-world rent,
      but a filing rate near 6%. The variable that lines up with the geography
      is not the rental market; it is the legal apparatus around eviction.
    </p>
    <p>
      In states tinted sage, tenants have at least one of three things: a right
      to counsel in eviction court, a just-cause requirement that landlords
      explain why they are filing, or aggressive sealing of eviction records so
      that one filing does not blacklist a tenant from future rentals. In the
      un-tinted states, a landlord can typically file by paying a small court
      fee, with no obligation to show cause and no automatic counsel for the
      tenant. The cost of filing is low; the volume of filings rises to meet
      it. The map is what that procedural difference looks like at scale.
    </p>
    <p>
      None of this is invisible — Eviction Lab researchers, legal aid lawyers,
      and the cities themselves know it. What a map can do that a paper can't
      is collapse the explanation into a single look. The same renter, with
      the same back-rent, in the same kind of building, faces dramatically
      different odds depending on which side of which state line their unit
      sits on.
    </p>
    <p class="aside">
      <em>A small disclosure.</em> Filing counts and rates are reconstructed
      from the Eviction Lab's monthly Eviction Tracking System and its 2025
      preliminary report (April 2026). Tenant-protection categorisation here
      is binary; the Legal Services Corporation's database scores along
      multiple dimensions, and several states sit on the boundary. The map
      reflects 41 cities and 10 states only — coverage is not nationwide
      because state court records vary in public access.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div slot="notebook-zh">
    <p>
      多数驱逐不上新闻，因为它们一次只发生一起。所以即便这个数字本身巨大，
      地图上呈现的总量对大多数人来说仍然陌生：123 万起驱逐起诉，发生在
      41 个美国城市，相当于每 13 户租客中就有 1 起。这张地图请读者
      正视一个通常只被埋在一句话里的数字。
    </p>
    <p>
      这些点不分布在租金最高的地方。纽约的租金是世界顶级的，filing rate
      只有 5%；亚特兰大的中位租金大约是纽约的一半，filing rate 是 19.8%——
      去年每五户亚特兰大租客中就有一户面对过驱逐起诉。费城是类似的故事：
      真实的高租金，filing rate 大约 6%。能与这片地理对得上的变量
      不是租房市场，而是关于驱逐的<em>法律装置</em>。
    </p>
    <p>
      染浅 sage 色的州，租客至少拥有以下三项中的一项：在驱逐法庭中有权
      获得律师协助 (right-to-counsel)、房东必须证明"正当理由" (just-cause)
      才能起诉、或者主动封存驱逐记录使一次起诉不至于让租客被未来租房
      市场拉黑。没染色的州，房东只需缴一笔小额法庭费用就能发起驱逐，
      不需要证明任何理由，租客也没有自动配置律师。filing 的成本越低，
      filing 的数量就涨到与那个低成本相称。这张地图，就是那种程序差异
      在大尺度上的样子。
    </p>
    <p>
      这一切并不是隐性的——Eviction Lab 的研究者、法援律师、以及这些
      城市本身都清楚。地图能做、论文不能做的一件事，是把解释折叠成
      一眼。同样一个租客、同样的欠租金额、同样的住房类型，他/她
      会因为住房单位落在哪条州界的哪一边，面对完全不同的胜负概率。
    </p>
    <p class="aside">
      <em>附注：</em>filing 数量与 rate 由 Eviction Lab 的月度 Eviction
      Tracking System 与其 2025 年初步报告（2026 年 4 月）重构。租客
      保护的分类此处采用二元划分；Legal Services Corporation 数据库
      为多维评分，部分州处于边界。本图覆盖 41 个城市与 10 个州，
      并非全国——美国各州法院记录的公开程度差异很大。
    </p>
  </div>

  <ul slot="provenance-en">
    <li>City filing counts and rates: <a href="https://evictionlab.org/eviction-tracking/get-the-data/" rel="noopener">Eviction Lab — Eviction Tracking System</a> (2025 monthly aggregates).</li>
    <li>2025 trends and benchmark numbers: <a href="https://evictionlab.org/ets-report-2025/" rel="noopener">Eviction Lab — 2025 Preliminary Analysis</a>, April 2026.</li>
    <li>Tenant-protection categorisation: <a href="https://www.lsc.gov/initiatives/effect-state-local-laws-evictions/lsc-eviction-laws-database" rel="noopener">LSC Eviction Laws Database</a> + <a href="https://civilrighttocounsel.org/map" rel="noopener">NCCRC right-to-counsel map</a>.</li>
    <li>Renter household denominators (for filing rates): <a href="https://data.census.gov/" rel="noopener">ACS 5-year (2018–2023)</a>, table B25033.</li>
    <li>State geometry: <a href="https://github.com/topojson/us-atlas" rel="noopener"><code>us-atlas@3 states-10m</code></a> via jsDelivr.</li>
    <li>Source map &amp; build script: <code>src/pages/friday-harbor/2026-04-27-1-23-million-eviction-filings.astro</code>.</li>
  </ul>

  <ul slot="provenance-zh">
    <li>城市 filing 数量与 rate：<a href="https://evictionlab.org/eviction-tracking/get-the-data/" rel="noopener">Eviction Lab — Eviction Tracking System</a>（2025 月度汇总）。</li>
    <li>2025 趋势与基准数据：<a href="https://evictionlab.org/ets-report-2025/" rel="noopener">Eviction Lab 2025 初步分析报告</a>（2026 年 4 月）。</li>
    <li>租客保护分类：<a href="https://www.lsc.gov/initiatives/effect-state-local-laws-evictions/lsc-eviction-laws-database" rel="noopener">LSC 驱逐法律数据库</a> + <a href="https://civilrighttocounsel.org/map" rel="noopener">NCCRC 法律咨询权地图</a>。</li>
    <li>租客户数（filing rate 分母）：<a href="https://data.census.gov/" rel="noopener">ACS 5-year (2018–2023)</a> 表 B25033。</li>
    <li>美国州界几何：<a href="https://github.com/topojson/us-atlas" rel="noopener"><code>us-atlas@3 states-10m</code></a>，经 jsDelivr 加载。</li>
    <li>源码与构建脚本：<code>src/pages/friday-harbor/2026-04-27-1-23-million-eviction-filings.astro</code>。</li>
  </ul>
</FridayHarborLayout>

<style>
  .evic-figure { margin: 0; }
  .evic-stage {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 10;
    background: transparent;
    border: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
  }
  .evic-stage svg { display: block; width: 100%; height: 100%; }
  .map-status {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .evic-figure figcaption {
    margin: 1.1rem 0.2rem 0;
    font-size: 0.94rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-family: var(--serif);
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 880px;
  }
  .evic-figure figcaption b { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 500; }
  .evic-figure figcaption em { color: var(--uw-purple-deep); font-style: italic; }
  .evic-figure figcaption .legend-line {
    display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 0.55rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
  }
  .evic-figure figcaption .legend-swatch {
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }
  .swatch-rtc {
    width: 22px; height: 14px;
    background: var(--sage-soft);
    border: 1px solid rgba(108,99,88,0.35);
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .swatch-evic-major {
    width: 14px; height: 14px;
    background: #8a3e2e;
    border: 2px solid var(--rose);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(194,160,148,0.32);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }
  .aside {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--rule);
    padding-left: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-size: 0.88rem !important;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .evic-stats {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1.4rem;
    margin: 1.4rem 0.2rem 0;
    padding: 1rem 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .evic-stats .stat {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.2rem;
  }
  .evic-stats .stat-num {
    font-family: var(--display, "Cormorant Garamond", Georgia, serif);
    font-size: 1.85rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--uw-purple-deep);
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums lining-nums;
  }
  .evic-stats .stat-num small {
    font-size: 0.55em;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-left: 0.1em;
  }
  .evic-stats .stat-label {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    max-width: 14em;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .evic-stats { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1rem; }
  }
</style>

